Uses of Package
suncertify.db

  • Packages that use suncertify.db 
    Package Description
    suncertify.db
    This package holds the classes relevant to all the operations around processing and interacting with the db file and DBCache.
    suncertify.model
    This package holds the classes relating to the Model of the MVC architecture and also the Room object.
    suncertify.server
    This package holds the classes relevant to the networked aspect of the application, how it is set up and how it is accessed remotely.
    suncertify.view
    This package holds the View of the MVC architecture and hence all the GUI classes.
  • Classes in suncertify.db used by suncertify.db 
    Class and Description
    DatabaseFailureException
    This exception is used when there is a issue connecting to the database or accessing records.
    DBAccess 
    DBAccessExtended
    This interface is used to add additional methods to ones provided in DBAccess interface
    DuplicateKeyException
    Duplicate Key exception.
    RecordNotFoundException
    This exception is thrown went a record does not exist or is marked as deleted in the database file.
    SecurityException
    Security exception thrown if incorrect cookie used to try unlock a locked record.
